      • setRelink

        public void setRelink(java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle relink)
        Description copied from interface: RelinkableCallSite
        Sets the relink method. This is a method matching the method type of the call site that will try to discover the adequate target for the invocation and then subsequently invoke RelinkableCallSite.setGuardedInvocation(GuardedInvocation). This method is normally only called by the DynamicLinker implementation.
        Specified by:
        setRelink in interface RelinkableCallSite
        Parameters:
        relink - the relink method handle.

      • setGuardedInvocation

        public void setGuardedInvocation(GuardedInvocation guardedInvocation)
        Description copied from interface: RelinkableCallSite
        This method will be called once by the dynamic linker every time the call site is relinked.
        Specified by:
        setGuardedInvocation in interface RelinkableCallSite
        Parameters:
        guardedInvocation - the guarded invocation that the call site should set as its current target. Note that the call sites are allowed to keep other non-invalidated invocations around for implementation of polymorphic inline caches.
